WhatsApp-Based Accounts Automation (MVP) Developer
Handover Document
1. Objective
Build a WhatsApp bot to capture Purchase, Payment, and Expense entries; manage Vendor Ledger; and enforce
Confirmation + Approval workflows using Text, Voice, and Image inputs.
2. Core Features
Data Entry
• Purchase entry
• Payment entry
• Expense entry
Vendor Types
• Credit (running balance)
• Bill-to-Bill (invoice-based)
• Advance (prepaid adjustment)
Input Modes
• Text
• Voice
• Image (bill, ledger, payment proof)
3. Complete Flow
User Input (Text/Voice/Image) → Data Extraction → Duplicate Check → Confirmation (same media) → Save as
Pending → Approval Flow → (Optional Edit by Approver) → Final Approval → Ledger Update → Response to user
4. Input Processing
Text
Rule-based + AI parsing.
Voice
Speech-to-text → parse.
Image
OCR → parse; store image in cloud and save URL.
5. Confirmation Layer (Mandatory)
System must repeat extracted data in the same media type as input. Actions: OK → proceed; EDIT → modify;
CANCEL → discard.
6. Duplicate Detection
• Image hash comparison
• Transaction reference ID (UPI) check
• Vendor + Amount + Time similarity check
• Exact duplicate → block; possible duplicate → ask user
7. Transaction States
Status Description
Temp Before confirmation
Pending Waiting for approval
Approved Final
Rejected Discarded
8. Approval Workflow
Created By Can Approve
Father Brother / Me
Brother Me
Me Auto-approved
Actions: Approve, Reject, Edit (then approve).
9. Edit at Approval
Allowed only in Pending state. Editable fields: Vendor, Amount, Mode, Type. Must maintain audit log of changes.
10. Ledger Logic
• Credit: Running balance
• Bill-to-Bill: Map payment to invoice
• Advance: Payment creates advance; purchase reduces it
11. Time Handling
• created_at
• transaction_time
• approved_at
12. Image Handling
• Download from WhatsApp
• Upload to cloud (Google Drive)
• Store URL in database
• Link to transaction
13. Database (MVP)
Transactions
• id, vendor, type, amount, mode, vendor_type
• status, created_by, approved_by
• created_at, approved_at, transaction_time
• image_url, txn_hash, image_hash, reference_id
Vendors
• name, type, balance
Audit Logs
• txn_id, field_changed, old_value, new_value, edited_by, timestamp
14. Data Retrieval Commands
• LEDGER
• SUMMARY TODAY / MONTH
• SEARCH
• PENDING